args:
In the midst of the party's battle with Morsayati,
Augus uses the army's most powerful weapon,
but it has no effect. The people are distraught,
but Ilia and the Holywyrm preach to them,
convincing everyone that this is the time for
dragons and humans to join forces.
Stop! I thought your target was Elysium!
What will come from hurting others?!\nWhat can you possibly hope to gain?!
I won't forgive Elysium...\nI won't forgive the WORLD!
Now what is he going to do?!
I don't see how we can hope to win when\nwe can barely defend against his attacks.
No! It's Augus and the army!
This raw power is enough to destroy the\ncapital and the forest, human and dragon\nalike! Ah, it is truly wonderful!
With this power, all of the world will\nfinally be in our grasp...
And I will rule over it as a GOD!
Ha! A god of crap, maybe!
You will eat those words, girl!
Behold Dies Irae, our manatech weapon!
It's a mana cannon—and it's massive!
That thing is powerful enough to\nwipe out entire landscapes!
Yes... YES! It worked! Aaaah ha ha ha ha!
This is the power of a god...\nSomething we do not possess...\nOh, how I've longed for this!
The light of the god is burning me away!\nYes! Yeeeeeeees! Take me, O lord!
Th-this can't be... That cannon was the\ncutting edge of our military R&D!
That thing killed Augus!\nWhat're we gonna do?!
Your enemy is trying to lay waste to the\nentire world—there IS nowhere to run.
Then this is it! We're all going to die!
There is a way yet remaining to you,\nhuman whelps.
It's the dragon that was fighting\nthe monster!
This world teeters at the precipice of crisis;\non the verge of losing all order and\ntumbling headlong into utter ruination.
Fight alongside us dragons, and set your\nsights upon a new and better world.
The world does not meet its end this day!
You've got people you love, right?\nPeople you want to save?
If so, then the time has come to choose:\nWill you cower or face what awaits us?\nWill you die or will you live?
The correct door will only open for those\nwho make a bold choice!
I...I don't want to die...\nI believe in you, Ilia!
I WILL see my family again!
People and dragons now act as one!
Prayers from people all across the world\nare carrying mana to this place.
It has been entrusted to us—and I\nknow now what I must do.
As the Auspex, I will play steward to\nthese prayers and mana in order to\nsummon forth an even greater light!
O abundant mana! Grant us your strength!\nBestow upon us the future we seek!
I am Zethia, she chosen by holy mana!\nAnd now, I shall guide it home!
The mana is obeying Zethia...\nIs THIS her power?!
Answer these prayers and become as light!\nPurify calamity and bring peace to all!
(You were always the one looking out for\nme, my brother...)
(But now, I will do my part for you—\nand for our future!)
...Huh? How odd. I thought I heard\nZethia's voice just now.
I feel like it's not possible. I mean,\nwe don't even know where that\nstrange man spirited her off to...
But if I heard it AND you heard it, Notte...
I wonder where Zethia is now?
I don't know—but I DO know that we need\nto set our sights on getting her back and\nmake that our overriding goal.
...Will you pray with me, Notte?\nPray that Zethia is safe, I mean.
Oh, for sure—but let's tag a ＂We hope we\nget to see her again＂ onto the end.
No matter where we are, we love and\nsupport Zethia always. May those feelings\nfind their way to her...
(I just felt the faint whisper of his mana.\nI have received his prayers.)
(No matter how far apart we might be,\nI will continue to hold faith in my brother\nand all of our friends.)
Ilia! Use our power to protect this world!
Thanks, Zethia! I know we can do it!
That calamity goes beyond anything\nwe could ever conceive of...
Any of us could die in the battle to come,\nbut we still have to fight.
The decision is made: We will fight\nto protect those that we love!
The future of this world relies on our\nactions this day. Seize this moment!
I will fight fate itself to see everyone safe!\nEn garde, Morsayati!
